<TITLE> Tarique follows Coco in paying last respects to grandmother </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  The body of former prime minister Khaleda Zia's mother Toyeba Majumdar arrived in Dhaka Saturday afternoon. Khaleda's son Arafat Rahman Coco was the first to pay his last respects to his grandmother. Tarique in white punjabi was led into Khaleda's cantonment home at 5.52pm, minutes after Coco left for Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University hospital. Coco arrived on Shaheed Mainul Road at 4:36pm to view the body of his grandmother, IG (prisons) Brigadier General Zakir Hassan told bdnews24.com. He left the place at 5.48pm. The official had earlier said the threeKhaleda and sons Tarique Rahman and Cocowould not be allowed to see the body together. They may not take part in the namaz-e-janaza for Toyeba at Azad Mosque in Gulshan. Zakir Hassan said Khaleda Zia would get two hours to stay beside her mother's body. Tarique and Coco were allocated one hour each. Their parole could be extended to 9pm, Zakir added. bdnews24.
